The deal is part of a greater acquisition announced by SunEdison also on 7 May 2015, pursuant to which the U.S. firm has signed definitive agreements for the purchase of renewable energy portfolios also in Brazil, Chile, China, India, Peru and South Africa. The Alto Cielo project is located in the Artigas Department in northwestern Uruguau and is still under construction. ORIGINAL: U.S. renewable energy development company SunEdison Inc has signed a definitive agreement to acquire 336 MW of operating wind and hydropower assets from Brazilian peer Renova Energia SA for BRL 1.613bn (USD 527.8mn). The buyer acted through its recently created subsidiary TerraForm Global Inc. Under the agreement, SunEdison will acquire a portfolio of 336 MW composed of operating wind and hydropower assets from Renova. Additionally, the company is also entitled to a Third Party Right of First Offer (ROFO) which grants SunEdison the right to purchase up to 1,870 MW of renewable energy projects, of which 534 MW are operating projects and the remaining under development. The payment can be exercised through either cash or stock options. The transaction is subject to the achievement of an Initial Public Offering (IPO) by TerraForm Global, the fulfillment of certain conditions precedent and attainment of regulatory approvals from the Brazilian Council for Economic Defense (CADE), the National Electric Energy Agency (ANEEL) and Brazilian electric utilities company Eletrobras SA. SunEdison has also signed a Letter of Intent (LoI) stating its interest in acquiring a 16% stake in Renova. Renova Energia SA, created in 2001, specialises in the generation and sale of electric energy through alternative renewable sources, with a focus on wind energy generation, solar power and small hydroelectric plants. The company has a portfolio of energy projects with 2.3 GW of contracted installed capacity throughout Brazil. Renova is listed on the BM&FBovespa Stock Exchange. SunEdison Inc, established in 1984 and located in Belmont, California, develops, finances, installs and operates renewable power plants. It is the world's largest renewable energy development company. SunEdison has installations and manufacturing plants and 39 offices located throughout North America, Europe and Asia, and employs more than 6,000 people. SunEdison posted USD 2.48bn in revenues and a net loss of USD 1.18mn in 2014. The company is listed on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE). ______________________________________________________________________________ UPDATE: A Renova disse em seu relatório anual para 2015, que em 18 de setembro de 2015, concluiu com sucesso a primeira fase do acordo, relativamente a venda do portfólio de 336 MW de ativos eólicos e hidroeléctricos. A Renova também revelou que a subsidiária da SunEdison, TerraForm Global Inc, cancelou a segunda parte do projeto, relativamente ao projeto de 1,336 MW de projectos ainda em desenvolvimento. In case Galane purchases the remaining shares, all Galaxy shareholders will own 31.8% of Galane's enlarged capital on a non-diluted basis, or 36.6% on a diluted-basis. Galane Gold said that this acquisition is aligned with its strategy of acquiring production or near-term production assets. The transaction is subject to regulatory and other approvals and is expected to close on or before 30 June 2015. Deadline for completion can be unilaterally extended by Galane to 31 August 2015. Galaxy Gold operates mining assets situated on the Barberton Greenstone Belt, 10km west of the city of Barberton in the Mpumalanga Province of South Africa. The buyer acted together with its wholly-owned subsidiary Secil - Companhia Geral de Cal e Cimento SA, via their jointly-owned Brazilian holding company NSOSPE Empreendimentos e Participacoes SA. With the acquisition, Semapa now indirectly owns 100% of the target's total capital. The transaction is subject to regulatory approvals and the fulfillment of certain conditions. Supremo Cimentos SA, founded in 2003, is a manufacturer of compost and pozzolanic Portland cement. The company operates a clinker and cement plant in Pomerode, Santa Catarina state. The company recently finished the construction of an industrial facility with expected annual capacity of 750,000 tonnes of concrete in the city of Adrianopolis. Secil - Companhia Geral de Cal e Cimento SA, founded in 1930, specialises in manufacturing and distribution of grey and white cement and related products. The company operates three production facilities in Portugal with annual production capacity of 4mn tonnes of cement and exports its products to Spain, Tunisia, Angola, France, Lebanon and Cape Verde. Secil is listed on the Euronext Lisbon Stock Exchange. Semapa - Sociedade de Investimento e Gestao SGPS SA, established in 1991, is an industrial holding comprising three companies: Portucel Group, manufacturer of paper and pulp, Secil Group, producer of concretes and aggregates, and environmental company Etsa Group. With a team of over 5,000 employees, the company is present in Europe, Middle East, Africa, North and South America. Semapa posted EUR 2bn (USD 852mn) in revenues and a net profit of EUR 112.8 (USD 48.07mn) in 2014, a decrease of 22.8% year-on-year basis. ExxonMobil, Royal Dutch Shell, Total and BP have had interests in the concession since the 1970s but the agreements with them expired in January 2014. The concession covers 15 principal onshore oil fields of Abu Dhabi and represents more than half of the Emirate's production. It will be operated by newly established company Abu Dhabi Company for Onshore Petroleum Operations Limited (ADCO). Inpex Corp recorded revenues of JPY 1.33bn (USD 11bn) and net profit of JPY 183.7bn (USD 1.52bn) in 2014. Inpex has been present in the UAE for over 40 years. It has participating interests in Umm Shaif, Lower Zakum, Umm Lulu, Nasr, Upper Zakum, Umm Al-Dalkh, Satah and Abu Al Bukoosh (ABK) oil fields. ORIGINAL: U.S.-based industrial real estate company Prologis has acquired warehousing facility Westgate Park Rudna in the Czech Republic from Czech real estate firm The Charnwood Company and U.K.-based real estate investment manager Europa Capital, the daily Hospodarske Noviny said. According to the daily, the deal value is around CZK 650mn (EUR 23.9mn). In September 2014, Prologis purchased a 230,000 m2 logistics portfolio in the Czech Republic, Poland and Slovakia. Westgate Park Rudna is located west of Prague, at exit 5 of the D5 Highway. It offers up to 13,000 m2 of dry storage space, 7,600 m2 of chilled and frozen storage premises, 1,200 m2 of secured mezzanine storage area and more than 6,000 m2 of modern office space for lease. Prologis, founded in 1983, is an owner, developer and operator of industrial real estate, focused on global and regional markets across the Americas, Europe and Asia. The company is also engaged in the leasing of modern distribution facilities. Its portfolio consists of approximately 2,900 industrial properties. It has USD 53bn in total assets under management. The company reported revenues of USD 1.53bn with a workforce of over 1,500 for 2014. Prologis owns and manages 55 million m2 of logistics and distribution space. Europa Capital is a real estate fund manager operating across Europe. Since 1995, it has raised seven real estate funds and committed to over 80 transactions totalling some EUR 8bn across 18 European countries. The Charnwood Company was founded in 2001. UPDATE 1: On 7 May 2015, the Brazilian antitrust competition regulator CADE gave its approval for the deal. ORIGINAL: U.S. private equity firm The Carlyle Group LP announced a primary equity investment in Brazilian hospital operator Rede D'Or Sao Luiz SA. Rede D'Or is currently held by the Moll family, local founder and majority shareholder, and Banco BTG Pactual SA. According to market sources, the deal is valued at BRL 1.75bn (USD 591.52mn) for an 8.3% stake of Rede D'Or's increased capital. The same sources said that BTG will reduce its shareholding from 25.6% to 23.6% while the Moll family's interest will decrease from 74.4% to 68.1%. Carlyle acted through its affiliates Carlyle Partners VI, through its South American buyout funds and Fundo Brasil de Internacionalizacao de Empresas FIP II (FBIE II). The transaction is expected to close in the second quarter of 2015. The investment will be used for the future growth plans of Rede D'Or, which include the construction of new hospitals, expansion of existing facilities, and the financing of new acquisitions. The hospital group intends to invest some BRL 1.5bn in 2015 in existing and new facilities. Sources close to the deal also said that Carlyle is expected to make a second capital injection in the target to acquire up to 10%. Rede D'Or Sao Luiz SA, established in 1977 by the Moll family in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, operates a network of 27 hospitals with over 4,500 beds and 46 laboratories under the Labs D'Or brand, located in the states of Rio de Janeiro, Sao Paulo, Pernambuco and the Federal District. With a team of more than 33,000 employees and 85,000 affiliated doctors, annually, the company has over 2.7 million emergency room visits, 170,000 surgeries and 270,000 inpatient treatments, serving an addressable market of 53 million people. According to Reuters, Rede D'Or had revenues of BRL 5.5bn and EBITDA of BRL 930mn in 2014. Banco BTG Pactual SA, founded in 1983 by Brazilian entrepreneur Andre Esteves, is a leading provider of investment banking, asset and wealth management services in Brazil. The group has an international investment and distribution platform with a team of more than 3,000 professionals across offices throughout Latin America, the United States, the United Kingdom, Singapore and Hong Kong. BTG Pactual posted a net income of BRL 1.9bn (USD 707.5bn) in 2014. BTG is listed on the BM&FBovespa Stock Exchange. The The Carlyle Group LP, established in 1987, is a global alternative investment firm with USD 194bn in assets under management across 128 funds and 142 fund of funds vehicles as of 31 December 2014. With a team of more than 1,650 professionals in 40 offices across six continents, the company specialises in private equity investments in the aerospace, defense, consumer and retail, energy, financial services, healthcare, industrial, technology and business services, telecommunications, media and transportation sectors. The Carlyle Group is listed on the NASDAQ Stock Market. _____________________________________________________________________________________ UPDATE: Em 7 de maio de 2015, o Conselho Administrativo de Defesa Econômica (CADE) deu o seu aval a operação. As mesmas fontes disseram que o BTG diminuiu sua participação de 25.6% para 23.6% e a posição da família Moll foi reduzida de 74.4% para 68.1%. A transação deverá ser concluída no segundo trimestre de 2015. O investimento está em linha com os planos de crescimento da empresa-alvo, que incluem a construção de novos hospitais, ampliação das instalações existentes, bem como o financiamento de novas aquisições. O hospital pretende investir BRL 1.5bn em 2015 em empreendimentos novos e renovação de outros já detidos. Fontes próximas ao negócio dizem que o Carlyle estima fazer uma segunda injecção de capital na empresa-alvo para aumentar sua participação até 10%. A Rede D'Or, fundada em 1977 pela família Moll, no Rio de Janeiro, Brasil,, opera uma rede de 27 hospitais com mais de 4,500 camas e 46 laboratórios sob a marca Labs D'Or, localizados nos estados do Rio de Janeiro, São Paulo, Pernambuco e no Distrito Federal. Com uma equipe de mais de 33,000 funcionários e 85,000 médicos afiliados, anualmente o grupo tem mais de 2.7 milhões de atendimentos de emergência, 170,000 cirurgias e 270,000 tratamentos de internação, servindo um mercado potencial de 53 milhões de pessoas. De acordo com a agência Reuters, a Rede D'Or postou receitas de BRL 5.5bn e um EBITDA de BRL 930mn em 2014. O BTG Pactual, fundado em 1983 pelo empresário brasileiro André Esteves, é um provedor líder de serviços de banco de investimento e gestão de ativos e fortunas no Brasil. O grupo tem uma plataforma internacional de investimentos e distribuição com uma equipe de mais de 2,800 profissionais em escritórios na América Latina, Estados Unidos, Reino Unido, Cingapura e Hong Kong. O BTG Pactual está listado na Bolsa de Valores de São Paulo BM&FBovespa e apresentou um lucro líquido de BRL 2.8bn (USD 1.3bn) em 2014. O Carlyle Group LP, fundado em 1987, é uma empresa global de investimentos alternativos com USD 194bn em ativos sob gestão distribuídos em 128 fundos e 142 fundos de fundos em 31 de dezembro de 2014. Com uma equipe de 1,650 profissionais em 40 escritórios em seis continentes, a empresa é especializada em investimentos em participações nos setores aeroespacial, defesa, varejo, energia, serviços financeiros, saúde, industria, tecnologia, serviços de negócios, telecomunicações, mídia e transporte. Alstom develops and markets systems, equipment and services for the railway sector, with the widest range of solutions in the market - from high-speed trains to metros and tramways - and associated maintenance, modernisation, infrastructure and signalling solutions. The group is present in over 60 countries, and following the deal it will employ 32,000 people. For 2014, it reported sales of EUR 6.2bn. GE is a multinational industrial and financial conglomerate with interests in the energy, oil and gas, mining, power and water, healthcare, transportation, technology infrastructure, aviation, capital finance, intelligent platforms and customized industrial solutions. The company reported sales revenues of USD 148.5bn and net income of USD 15.23bn for 2014. GE's power and water division produces heavy-duty gas turbines and machines for utilities and independent power producers. The accord foresees the incorporation of their asset-management businesses Pioneer Global Asset Management SpA and Santander Asset Management SA SGIIC, respectively, into a new company named Pioneer Investments. Santander will have a direct 33.3% stake in the new company, UniCredit a 33.3% shareholding, and U.S. private equity fund managers Warburg Pincus LLC and General Atlantic LLC will share a 33.3% stake. The agreement also stipulates that Pioneer's operations in the United States won't be included in the new company but will be owned by UniCredit (50%) and Warburg Pincus and General Atlantic (50%). The current CEO of Santander Asset, Mr. Juan Alcaraz, will keep the same position in the new company, whereas Mr. Giordano Lombardo, CEO and CIO of Pioneer Global, will be appointed Chief Investment Officer of the new company. In addition, as part of the deal, Warburg and General Atlantic will make an equity investment into the target. The purpose of the operation is to provide the new company with greater diversification, in both mature and high growth markets, in terms of products, client base and distribution channels. Closing is subject to customary regulatory and corporate approvals and the fulfilment of certain conditions precedent. Pioneer Global Asset Management SpA, founded in 1928, provides investment solutions such as mutual funds, alternative investments, capital protection and absolute return products to institutions, corporations, intermediaries and private investors around the world. The firm employs over 2,000 professionals in 28 countries. As of 30 March 2015, the company's assets under management totalled to EUR 225bn (USD 242bn). Santander Asset Management SA SGIIC, founded in 1985 and based in Madrid, is a privately-owned investment manager. The firm is engaged in the management of separate client focused equity, fixed income, and balanced portfolios, as well as launching and managing equity, fixed income, and balanced mutual funds for its clients. Banco Santander SA, established in 1857, is the largest financial group in Spain with operations in ten countries in Europe, North America and South America. With a team of 183,000 employees, the company operates a network of 13,927 branches, serving more than 106 million clients. Santander registered a net income of EUR 5.816bn (USD 7.07bn) in 2014. Its total assets amounted to EUR 1.37trn (USD 1.48trn) as of 31 March 2015. The company is listed on the Madrid, Mexican, London, New York, Euronext and Italian Stock Exchanges. UniCredit SpA, created in 1998 following the merger of several italian banks, is a global banking and financial services company. The company operates in 50 markets in 17 countries, with more than 8,500 branches and over 147,000 employees. Its key markets are Western and Eastern Europe. 106220 21/04/2015 保加利亚; 匈牙利; 斯洛伐克; 土耳其 Corn wet milling assets of Eaststarch in Bulgaria, Turkey and Hungary 收购 Archer Daniels Midland Co (ADM) 美国 食品制造 (311); 食品杂货批发 (4224); Tate & Lyle PLC 淀粉和植物脂肪和油制造业 (31122); 其他食品制造 (3119); 淀粉和植物脂肪和油制造业 (31122) 258.42 (DW 估计) 　 英国 并购 　 　 否 战略收购 已公布 资产; 现金 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 U.S.-based agricultural processor and food ingredient provider Archer Daniels Midland Company (ADM) said it will acquire 100% of corn wet mills in Bulgaria and Turkey, and a 50 %stake in a wet mill in Hungary from Eaststarch, its 50:50 joint venture with UK-based ingredients provider Tate & Lyle. In exchange, Tate & Lyle will receive a cash consideration of EUR 240mn (USD 258.4mn) and take the Eaststarch facility in Slovakia. The transaction is subject to regulatory approvals and is expected to close in the summer of 2015. Eaststarch was formed in 1992 and is engaged primarily in corn sweeteners and starches. In the year ended March 2014, the company had an operating profit of GBP 107mn (USD 178mn) and gross assets of GBP 518mn (USD 861.7mn). The predominantly bulk ingredients facilities in Bulgaria, Turkey and Hungary have a combined daily grind capacity of 200,000 bushels. Hungarian facility also produces ethanol for fuel, beverage and industrial uses. The transaction will increase ADM's global grind capacity for corn by 7.5%to three million bushels per day. Segundo os termos do acordo, a Harvest Minerals vai fazer vários pagamentos em dinheiro, totalizando AUD 6.3mn (USD 4.9mn) em diferentes períodos, programado para acontecer, em primeiro lugar, nas datas de assinatura do acordo; em segundo lugar, em 31 dezembro de 2015 e 2016, e 2017 até 2021; e em terceiro lugar, no início da produção comercial. The deal was made public by local news agency Reuters Brasil. Additional details were not disclosed. The seller acted through its investment fund Fundo de Investimento em Participacoes Coliseu (FIP Coliseu). Transmissora Alianca de Energia Eletrica SA (Taesa), founded in 2006, is an electricity transmission group, focused on the construction, operation and maintenance of electricity transmission infrastructure in Brazil. The company operates 6,250 km of transmission lines and 47 substations of between 230 and 500 Kv across the country an engages around 300 employees. Its main shareholders are state-owned Brazilian electrical power company CEMIG, controlled by the government of Minas Gerais, and local investment fund Fundo de Investimentos em Participacoes Coliseu. Taesa posted BRL 1.49bn (USD 556.7mn) in revenues and a net profit of BRL 904.85mn (USD 336.7mn) in 2014. The company is listed on the BM&FBovespa Stock Exchange. Banco Modal SA, established in 1995 in Rio de Janeiro, is a medium-sized multiple bank with operations in the areas of corporate banking, investment banking, asset management, structured financial products, securities trading and brokerage services. Its total assets amounted to BRL 1.5bn (USD 555.6mn) as of 31 December 2014. Its asset management unit Modal Administradora de Recursos manages BRL 2.5bn (USD 1.4bn) in committed capital, allocated in two private equity funds Oleo e Gas FIP and FIP Coliseu, focused on investments in the energy, oil and gas, and infrastructure sectors in Brazil. Empresas Publicas de Medellin ESP, founded in 1955 and headquartered in Medellin, Colombia, is a multi-utility company, operating in the energy, telecommunications, and water sectors in Colombia. ORIGINAL: French energy producer Albioma SA announced the acquisition of a 65% stake in Brazilian Codora Energia Ltda, owner of a bagasse-fuelled cogeneration plant in the state of Goias, for an undisclosed sum. According to the official press release, the operation will be financed by a combination of local debt and shareholders' equity. The plant, which currently injects 98 GWh of electricity to the power grid in Brazil, benefits from a long-term power purchase agreement covering the injection of 87 GWh per year at an inflation-indexed price of BRL 205 (USD 66.8) per MWh. The acquisition is subject to the fulfilment of certain conditions precedent and is expected to be completed during the second half of 2015. The Jalles Machado group will retain the remaining 35% in Codora. Codora Energia Ltda, established in 2006 and located in Goianesa, state of Goias, Brazil, is an electric power generation company focused on production and distribution of electricity, steam, hot water and air conditioning. Albioma SA, founded in 1982, specializes in the generation and sale of electric energy. The company operates a portfolio of thermal, anaerobic digestion and solar power generating plants with total installed capacity of 639 MW. Albioma is listed on the Euronext Paris Stock Exchange, and posted EUR 354mn (USD 131.7mn) in revenues and a net profit of EUR 38mn (USD 14.1mn) in 2014. ___________________________________________________________________________________________ A produtora de energia elétrica francesa Albioma SA anunciou a aquisição de uma participação de 65% na brasileira Codora Energia Ltda, proprietária de uma central de cogeração movida a bagaço de cana no estado de Goiás, por uma quantia não revelada. The buyer acted through its investment subsidiary RSP Fund No 6 LLC. U.S. venture capital firms Accel Partners also participated in the investment round. With the investment, Recruit plans to promote the use of crowdsourcing techniques in the design segment, which is expected to grow worldwide in future years. According to the official press release, 99designs will use the funds to enhance its global expansion strategy and develop new products. 99designs has substantial operations in Brazil, through its offices in Sao Paulo and Rio de Janeiro. Dan Strougo, Managing Director of the Latin America division of 99designs, said that the company's Brazilian website will be positively impacted by the new round of investment. He added that "among the expected changes are new payment methods, events for entrepreneurs and quality certification of designers" 99designs Pty Ltd, established in 2008 and based in Melbourne, Australia, specialises in the implementation and management of an online graphic design marketplace, which connects corporate clients with a network of more than 950,000 graphic designers from 192 countries. The company has additional offices in San Francisco, USA, Berlin, Germany and Paris, France. In April 2011, 99designs received a private equity funding of USD 35mn from US venture capital firm Accel Partners and a group of angel investors, and started its globalisation strategy with the acquisition of German design marketplace 12Designer in August 2012. Accel Partners, founded in 1983 in Palo Alto, California, is an early and growth stage venture capital firm with over USD 6bn in assets under management, focused mainly on internet technology companies. With offices in Silicon Valley, New York, London, China, and India, the company has investments in 300 start-ups in the United States, Europe, Asia and Latin America. Recruit Holdings Co Ltd, founded in 1960 and headquartered in Tokyo, Japan, provides information and human resources services. It has over 30,000 employees and has operation in Asia, the Americas, Europe and Oceania. In consideration for the 50% interest in the oil block, New Times Energy will drill, log, test and complete an exploration well of a depth of 2,900 metres, and will pay all the costs incurred in the amount of approximately USD 8mn. New Times Energy acted via the Argentinean subsidiary of its wholly-owned affiliate High Luck Group Ltd. The Hong Kong-based firm, which will be in charge of the exploration, development and production of the oil block, added that this acquisition will expand the company's presence in Argentina. The Chirete oil block has an area of 1,793 square kilometres and is located in the Argentinean province Salta. The sale is aligned with the sales process of Petrobras' Argentinean operations announced back in September 2014, which was delayed as the company was involved in a corruption scandal that led to the resignation in February 2015 of then CEO Maria das Gracas Silva Foster. Back on 2 March 2015, Petrobras revealed its plans to sell USD 13.7bn in assets during 2015 and 2016 as part of the company's efforts to reduce debt and protect cash. On 30 March 2015, Petrobras said that it has accepted the offer from Argentinean holding company Corporacion America SA, controlled by Argentinean entrepreneur Eduardo Eurnekian, pursuant to which Corporacion America, via its 70%-owned subsidiary Compania General de Combustibles SA (CGC), an Argentinean oil & gas firm, will acquire Petrobras' oil & gas assets located in the Austral Basin in the Argentinean province Santa Cruz for USD 101mn. New Times Energy is an investment holding company mainly engaged in general trading, oil exploration and exploitation. Currently, the company has oil and gas exploration projects in Argentina, the U.S. and China. It reported sales revenues of HKD 81.1mn (USD 10.5mn) and net loss of HKD 120.4mn (USD 15.5mn) for 2014. Petrobras is a state-owned multinational energy corporation, focused on exploration, production, refining, trade and transportation of oil and natural gas, petrochemicals and derivatives, electric energy, biofuels and other renewable energy source distribution. ORIGINAL: Mexico-focused Canadian miner Alamos Gold Inc, together with its compatriot peer AuRico Gold Inc, have jointly announced that they have agreed to merge. The parties will create a new, intermediate gold producer (MergeCo), which will later be renamed to Alamos Gold Inc. The new entity is estimated to have an equity value of USD 1.5bn. Under the agreement, all Alamos shareholders will receive one MergeCo share and USD 0.0001 in cash for each share they hold, while all of AuRico's shareholders will receive 0.5046 MergeCo shares for each share they hold. Following completion of the deal, which is structured as a merger of equals, Alamos and AuRico shareholders will each own approximately 50% of MergeCo. The transaction is subject to regulatory and other approvals, and is expected to close during the second quarter of 2015. In addition, a new company called AuRico Metals Inc (SpinCo) will be created, and will hold AuRico Gold's Kemess project in Canada and a 1.5% net smelter return royalty (NSR) on its Young-Davidson gold mine also in Canada, as well as AuRico's Fosterville and Stawell royalties. The SpinCo will be capitalized with USD 20mn in cash and will be owned 4.9% by MergeCo while the remaining shares will be distributed among Alamos and AuRico shareholders. The parties added that this merger will create a leading intermediate gold producer with diversified portfolio of assets, including two top-tier, cash flow-generating mines: AuRico's Young-Davidson in Ontario, Canada, and Alamos' Mulatos gold mine in the Mexican state Sonora. AuRico Gold is engaged in the exploration and production of gold in Mexico and Canada. The company reported sales revenues of USD 291.2mn and a net loss of USD 169.6mn for 2014. Alamos Gold develops, explores, mines and extracts precious metals mainly in Mexico. The company also has operations in Turkey and the United States. Under the terms of the transaction, RBS will manage the day to day management of the target until ownership is transferred to IndusInd Bank. Simultaneously, IndusInd Bank has entered into a partnership agreement with ABN Amro Bank to improve its risk management practices, client servicing and revenue streams. The Royal Bank of Scotland is a global banking and financial services firm headquartered in Edinburgh. It serves over 30 million clients through branches and operations across Europe, Asia, the Middle East, and North America. The Royal Bank of Scotland posted consolidated total assets of GBP 1,050.8bn (USD 1,632bn) for FY ended 31 December, 2014. IndusInd Bank provides financial products and services to consumer, corporate and public sector clients. It has 727 branches and 1,350 ATMs across India. 105965 10/04/2015 俄罗斯 Ford Sollers 少数股权购买 Ford Motor Company 美国 汽车及其他交通运输设备制造 (336); 　 　 汽车、摩托车及零配件批发 (4211) 　 　 　 　 并购 　 　 否 新股发行; 优先股 完成的 现金 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 U.S.-based car manufacturer Ford Motor Company has gained managing control over its JV with Russian peer Sollers - Ford Sollers, through the acquisition of newly-issued preference shares in the target, according to the 2014 financial results statement of Sollers and information of Kommersant daily. The two JV parties will retain parity in terms of common stock ownership. However, the newly-acquired prefs could gain voting rights in case no dividends are being paid to their holder, as legally regulated. Furthermore, an additional agreement was signed which stipulates that Sollers could sell its share in the JV to Ford Motor Company in the future at a price not lower than the minimum agreed one. The above agreements were reached in light of the difficult market conditions, the press release reads. Ford’s additional financing will be used for the fulfilment of Ford Sollers’ strategic tasks such as the release of new products and further investments in the localisation of components. The final target is increasing the operational efficiency and the market share. Ford Sollers was created in 2011. Ford Sollers was tasked to produce and distribute Ford-branded cars in Russia, using production facilities in Vsevolozhsk (the Leningrad region) with annual production capacity of 125,000 cars and Naberezhnye Chelny (the Republic of Tatarstan) with annual production capacity of 200,000 cars. 114592 09/04/2015 美国 Pereira & O'Dell LLC 收购 Pereira & O'Dell LLC 美国 广告、公共关系及相关服务 (5418); ABCDEFGHI Participacoes SA (Grupo ABC) 营销咨询服务 (541613); 广告、公共关系及相关服务 (5418); 广告、公共关系及相关服务 (5418) 　 　 70 巴西 并购 　 　 否 股份回购; 战略收购 完成的 现金 　 　 　 Shearman & Sterling LLP 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 U.S. advertising agency Pereira & O'Dell LLC has bought back around 70% of its shares from Brazilian communications group ABCDEFGHI Participacoes SA (Grupo ABC) for an undisclosed sum, media sources reported. Pereira & O'Dell LLC has gained back its independence from Grupo ABC, which provided it with financial backing during the last seven years. With its new independence, Pereira & O'Dell is expecting to accelerate its growth and to become more nimble in the fast developing international advertising industry. Mr. O'Dell, a founding partner of the U.S. agency, added that the company is ready to expand its offering to new countries. Pereira & O'Dell, established in 2008, provides advertising services internationally, through a combination of traditional advertising, digital, PR and design. The company operates offices in the U.S. (in the cities of New York and San Francisco), as well as in Brazil (in the cities of Porto Alegre and Sao Paulo). The agency's customer portfolio includes companies such as Skype, Intel, Coca-Cola, Dell, Nestle and others. Grupo ABC, founded in 2002 in Sao Paulo, is the 25th largest communications group in the world in 2015, according to American magazine Advertising Age. The group is comprised of 15 advertising, branding, and content services agencies in Brazil and the United States: Africa, Agencia Tudo, Asia, b!ferraz, DM9, DM9Rio, DM9Sul, Interbrand, Loducca, Morya, NewStyle, Pereira&O'Dell, Rockerheads, CDN and Sunset. It exports its products to over 40 countries. The company has branches in Brazil, Argentina, United States, Germany, Austria, China and Hungary, in addition to technical and commercial offices in France, England and Japan. Reflex Allen Group, founded in 1988 and based in Guiglia, Emilia-Romagna region, Italy, is a multinational company focused in the production of plastic tubes for fluids and brake system, spiral wire harnesses and safety labels, and provisions for vehicle manufacturers. The transaction will generate approximately EUR 13mn of free cash for GTC. The transaction is subject to customary closing conditions. Kazimierz Office Center is located in Krakow, in close proximity to the city center. Completed in 2009, it has five floors and offers 15,000 m2 of office space. GLL Real Estate Partners was founded in 2000 by three senior executives of HypoVereinsbank, in a joint venture with Lend Lease Corporation and Assicurazioni Generali. Today, the company is 81% owned by the management group and 19% owned by Generali Group. GLL Real Estate Partners' funds under management now exceed EUR 5bn with investments across Western Europe, Central Eastern Europe and the United States. GTC Group is a leading real estate developer in Central and Eastern Europe with current operations in Poland, Romania, Hungary, Croatia, Serbia, Bulgaria, Slovakia, the Czech Republic, Russia and Ukraine. ORIGINAL: Singaporean chemicals producer Matex International said it has agreed to acquire Hong Kong-registered coal mining company Blackgold Holdings HongKong from Australia-listed coal miner Blackgold International Holdings in a reserve takeover for SGD 475mn (USD 345.5mn). Through the deal, the factual buyer Blackgold International Holdings aims to provide a backdoor listing in Singapore for its subsidiary Blackgold Holdings HongKong. Upon completion of the deal, the shareholders of Blackgold International Holdings will hold a 95.7% stake in the enlarged capital of Matex International, which will subsequently shift its business focus from chemicals to coal mining. Matex International will satisfy the acquisition consideration with SGD 25mn in cash and with new own shares worth SGD 450mn that will be issued to the shareholders of Blackgold International Holdings and its related parties. Completion of the transaction is subject to certain conditions precedent, including regulatory approval. Blackgold Holdings HongKong owns and operates four underground thermal coal mines, namely Caotang, Heiwan, Baolong, and Changhong mines, all situated in Chongqing, China. As of 16 April 2014, the mines had combined proved and probable reserves of 100.7 million tonnes of ore. Matex International engages in the production, formulating, and sale of specialty chemicals for the textile industry worldwide. The company was established in 1989 and is currently listed on the Singapore Stock Exchange. 2016.04.12 　 360.88 　 　 　 　 　 负值 　 　 来源 1 来源 2
